# RESPONSES & REVISIONS — Locked decisions (July 2026)

Canonical copy: [playback-refactor/00-locked-decisions.md](./playback-refactor/00-locked-decisions.md)

- Subsystems communicate via **commands, snapshots, events** — not cross-mutation.
- **PlaybackSession** is framework-independent, app-lifetime, bootstrapped from `createPlaybackSession.ts`.
- **VC Mode** owns presentation/workflow only; does not own playback truth.
- **Play Lock** is VC-scoped; clears when VC exits.
- **Special between-song pause**: session `playbackPhase: waiting-for-host`; VC owns countdown UI.
- **No Scene** or presentation geometry in session.
- **Playlist order** resolved at next-track decision time from current library view.
- **Submission playlist protection** in library mutation layer when VC active + default id set.
- **AudioEffectsEngine** sibling; session holds intent only.
- **Song history** event-driven from session; preserve rich semantics.
- **Tests**: Electron-less characterization harness first; mock media adapters.
- **Input subsystem**: application-level peer (focus, routing, command generation) — not inside Playback or VC. Phase 4 adapters are interim bridges. See [09-future-enhancements.md](./playback-refactor/09-future-enhancements.md).
- **Commands evolve**: inventory is a product snapshot; architecture must absorb add/rename/remove without churn.
- **Scope**: infrastructure only — preserve behavior, improve ownership, no unrelated UX changes.

